{"parse":{"title":"Chemical colitis","pageid":6066515,"revid":793807795,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Chemical colitis</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Colitis\" title=\"Colitis\">colitis</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/Inflammation\" title=\"Inflammation\">inflammation</a> of the large <a href=\"/wiki/Intestine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Intestine\">intestine</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Colon_(anatomy)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Colon (anatomy)\">colon</a>, caused by the introduction of harsh chemicals to the colon by an <a href=\"/wiki/Enema\" title=\"Enema\">enema</a> or other procedure. Chemical colitis can resemble <a href=\"/wiki/Ulcerative_colitis\" title=\"Ulcerative colitis\">ulcerative colitis</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Infectious_colitis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Infectious colitis\">infectious colitis</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Pseudomembranous_colitis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pseudomembranous colitis\">pseudomembranous colitis</a> endoscopically.\n</p><p>Prior to 1950, <a href=\"/wiki/Hydrogen_peroxide\" title=\"Hydrogen peroxide\">hydrogen peroxide</a> enemas were commonly used for certain conditions. This practice will often result in chemical colitis.\n</p><p>Soap enemas may also cause chemical colitis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\nHarsh chemicals, such as <a href=\"/wiki/Chemical_compound\" title=\"Chemical compound\">compounds</a> used to clean <a href=\"/wiki/Colonoscopy\" title=\"Colonoscopy\">colonoscopes</a>, are sometimes accidentally introduced into the colon during <a href=\"/wiki/Colonoscopy\" title=\"Colonoscopy\">colonoscopy</a> or other procedures.  This can also lead to chemical colitis.\n</p><p>Chemical colitis may trigger a flare of ulcerative colitis or <a href=\"/wiki/Crohn%27s_colitis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Crohn&#39;s colitis\">Crohn's colitis</a>. Symptoms of colitis are assessed using the <a href=\"/wiki/Simple_Clinical_Colitis_Activity_Index\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Simple Clinical Colitis Activity Index\">Simple Clinical Colitis Activity Index</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Chemical_colitis&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">K. Harish, Severe colitis induced by soap enemas, Indian J. Gastroent., 2006 <cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20061016165312/http://www.indianjgastro.com/article.asp?issn=0254-8860%3Byear%3D2006%3Bvolume%3D25%3Bissue%3D2%3Bspage%3D99%3Bepage%3D100%3Baulast%3DK\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.indianjgastro.com/article.asp?issn%3D0254-8860%3Byear%3D2006%3Bvolume%3D25%3Bissue%3D2%3Bspage%3D99%3Bepage%3D100%3Baulast%3DK\">the original</a> on 2006-10-16<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2006-07-23</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.indianjgastro.com%2Farticle.asp%3Fissn%253D0254-8860%253Byear%253D2006%253Bvolume%253D25%253Bissue%253D2%253Bspage%253D99%253Bepage%253D100%253Baulast%253DK&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AChemical+colitis\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw1327\nCached time: 20180908041658\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic